Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Bothriochloa laguroides

Photo by Donald Burk, licensed under CC-BY-NC 4.0

Assembly is allelic, and the genome is hexaploid. It has a haploid genome size of 1700 Mb, and has 30 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Bothriochloa laguroides from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Dotplot of Bothriochloa laguroides vs.Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Bothriochloa laguroides along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Bothriochloa laguroides is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Bothriochloa laguroides

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Bothriochloa laguroides along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Bothriochloa laguroides is a hexaploid with an allelic, assembly, we expect 6 lines for each subgenome.
